<mageix_mws translate="label" module="ixcbadv">
                    <label>Advanced IXCBA&#174; Miscellaneous Settings</label>
                    <frontend_type>text</frontend_type>
                    <sort_order>1080</sort_order>
                    <show_in_default>1</show_in_default>
                    <show_in_website>1</show_in_website>
                    <show_in_store>1</show_in_store>
					<comment>
						<![CDATA[<br />
						<div class="custom-options">
							<div class="box">
								<p class="grand-total"><br /><b>Payment Action Description.</b></p>
								
								<br /><br />
								
								<p><b><font color = "red">How does SSL Certificate & IPN Setup affect Payment Action options.</b></br></font>All Payment Action options work best when IPN setup is working correctly. This means a valid SSL certificate (see list for SSL issuers accepted by Amazon:<a href="http://www.mageix.com/partners/id/5_3_tlid_61" target="_blank">Amazon Accepted SSL Certificates.</a> )<b> </b> </p>
								
								<br /><br />
								
								
								
								<p><b>Option 1. Sale (Instant Payment): </b>Authorize and Capture full amount immediately. Entire order is Invoiced automatically. <b>Recommended for normal Instant Payments. <font color = "red"> "Capture on Shipment" settings will be ignored if this is enabled.</font></b> </p>
								
								<p><br /><b>Option 2. Authorize (Capture when order is Invoiced - Single Invoicing):</b> This will Authorize the full order amount. You may then Capture the full authorized amount or lesser amount by invoicing the order.  </p><p><b>Recommended if you prefer or required to confirm or approve order first before collecting payment. Only 1 Invoice will be possible. Such orders MUST be invoiced within 7 days.<font color = "red">  If "Capture on Shipment is set to YES"; the entire order will be automatically captured on shipment, not on invoicing. </font></b><br /></p>
								
								<p><br /><b>Option 3. Deferred: (Authorize & Capture order is Invoiced - Multiple Invoicing) </b> This will neither Authorization nor Capture any amount. Instead, it simply confirms the order with Amazon. You may then collect payment by creating single invoice or multiple invoices within 30 days. Each invoice will Authorize & Capture an amount equal to the invoice amount.<b> <font color = "red">  If "Capture on Shipment is set to YES"; the entire order will be automatically captured on shipment, not on invoicing.</b></font></p><p><b> Recommended for Pre-Orders & Split Shipments. Single or Multiple Invoices possible. Such orders MUST be invoiced within 30 days.</b></p>
								
							</div>
						</div>
						]]>
					</comment>
